What is the difference between JVM and JRE?
JRE is an acronym for Java Runtime Environment.It is used to provide runtime environment.
It is the implementation of JVM.It physically exists.It contains set of libraries + other files that JVM uses at runtime. ... JDK is an acronym for Java Development Kit.
It physically exists.It contains JRE + development tools.
