What is the difference between stack and heap in Java?
The main difference between heap and stack is that stack memory is used to store local variables and function call while
heap memory is used to store objects in Java. ... 5) Variables stored in stacks are only visible to the owner
Thread while objects created in the heap are visible to all thread.

